  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Version: 1.7.1-unstable`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nFilters messages by this topic(s). Each topic must be a 4 bytes HEX string.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nlast version , i still can filter message by specified a partial topic, for example \"f3\" to filter all topic starts with 0xf3, it match topic \"0xf3aaaaaaa\" and \"0xf3000000\"\r\nthis version, i must specify a topic 4bytes length.\r\nwhy?\r\n\r\nfilter.go:\r\n func matchSingleTopic(topic TopicType, bt []byte) bool {\r\n\tif len(bt) > 4 {\r\n\t\tbt = bt[:4]\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfor j, b := range bt {\r\n\t\tif topic[j] != b {\r\n\t\t\treturn false\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn true\r\n}\r\nit still supports partial topic match",
